Borno State Governor Babagana Zulum has said that the state will be the first in the country to domesticate President Muhammadu Buhari’s policy on communication and digital economy. Governor Zulum stated this yesterday when he received the Minister of Communications and Digital Economy, Dr. Isa Ali Pantami, in Maiduguri the state capital. The governor also said his administration has digital literacy and skills acquisition as one of its top priority, which informs the creation of the Ministry of Science, Technology and Innovation. Earlier, Dr. Pantami commended Governor Zulum for the laudable and people-oriented programmes being executed in the state. The minster explained that his visit was to donate 100 laptops to the Borno State Government in its resolve to encourage digital literacy in Nigeria. He further stated that the donations are in compliance with President Buhari’s policy on communication and digital economy. FG to facilitate 95% digital literacy skills in Nigeria Our bad image scaring investors – Ministerial nominee NITDA honours Huawei with award for Digital Economy Promotion